g202.definition: [ἀκροατής] from ἀκροάομαι (to listen; apparently an intensive of {{g191}}); a hearer (merely)

g203.definition: [ἀκροβυστία] from {{g206}} and probably a modified form of πόσθη (the penis or male sexual organ); the prepuce; by implication, an uncircumcised (i.e. gentile, figuratively, unregenerate) state or person

g204.definition: [ἀκρογωνιαῖος] from {{g206}} and {{g1137}}; belonging to the extreme corner

g205.definition: [ἀκροθίνιον] from {{g206}} and θίς (a heap); properly (in the plural) the top of the heap, i.e. (by implication) best of the booty

g206.definition: [ἄκρον] neuter of an adjective probably akin to the base of {{g188}}; the extremity

g207.definition: [Ἀκύλας] probably for Latin  (an eagle); Akulas, an Israelite

g208.definition: [ἀκυρόω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2964}}; to invalidate

g209.definition: [ἀκωλύτως] adverb from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2967}}; in an unhindered manner, i.e. freely

g210.definition: [ἄκων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1635}}; unwilling

g211.definition: [ἀλάβαστρον] neuter of ἀλάβαστρος (of uncertain derivation), the name of a stone; properly, an "alabaster" box, i.e. (by extension) a perfume vase (of any material)

g214.definition: [ἀλαλάζω] from ἀλαλή ( a shout, "halloo"); to vociferate, i.e. (by implication) to wail; figuratively, to clang

g215.definition: [ἀλάλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2980}}; unspeakable

g216.definition: [ἄλαλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2980}}; mute

g218.definition: [ἀλείφω] from {{g1}} (as particle of union) and the base of {{g3045}}; to oil (with perfume)

g219.definition: [ἀλεκτοροφωνία] from {{g220}} and {{g5456}}; cock-crow, i.e. the third night-watch

g220.definition: [ἀλέκτωρ] from ἀλέκω (to ward off); a cock or male fowl

g221.definition: [Ἀλεξανδρεύς] from Ἀλεξάνδρεια (the city so called); an Alexandreian or inhabitant of Alexandria

g222.definition: [Ἀλεξανδρῖνος] from the same as {{g221}}; Alexandrine, or belonging to Alexandria

g223.definition: [Ἀλέξανδρος] from the same as (the first part of) {{g220}} and {{g435}}; man-defender; Alexander, the name of three Israelites and one other man

g226.definition: [ἀληθεύω] from {{g227}}; to be true (in doctrine and profession)

g227.definition: [ἀληθής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2990}}; true (as not concealing)

g229.definition: [ἀλήθω] from the same as {{g224}}; to grind

g231.definition: [ἁλιεύς] from {{g251}}; a sailor (as engaged on the salt water), i.e. (by implication) a fisher

g232.definition: [ἁλιεύω] from {{g231}}; to be a fisher, i.e. (by implication) to fish

g235.definition: [ἀλλά] neuter plural of {{g243}}; properly, other things, i.e. (adverbially) contrariwise (in many relations)

g238.definition: [ἀλληγορέω] from {{g243}} and ἀγορέω (to harangue (compare {{g58}})); to allegorize

g239.definition: [ἀλληλουϊα] of Hebrew origin (imperative of {{h1984}} and {{h3050}}); praise ye Jah!, an adoring exclamation

g240.definition: [ἀλλήλων] Genitive plural from {{g243}} reduplicated; one another

g241.definition: [ἀλλογενής] from {{g243}} and {{g1085}}; foreign, i.e. not a Jew

g242.definition: [ἅλλομαι] middle voice of apparently a primary verb; to jump; figuratively, to gush

g243.definition: [ἄλλος] a primary word; "else," i.e. different (in many applications)

g244.definition: [ἀλλοτριεπίσκοπος] from {{g245}} and {{g1985}}; overseeing others' affairs, i.e. a meddler (specially, in Gentile customs)

g245.definition: [ἀλλότριος] from {{g243}}; another's, i.e. not one's own; by extension foreign, not akin, hostile

g248.definition: [ἀλοάω] from the same as {{g257}}; to tread out grain

g249.definition: [ἄλογος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3056}}; irrational

g253.definition: [ἀλυπότερος] comparative of a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3077}}; more without grief

g254.definition: [ἅλυσις] of uncertain derivation; a fetter or manacle

g255.definition: [ἀλυσιτελής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g3081}}; gainless, i.e. (by implication) pernicious

g256.definition: [Ἀλφαῖος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h2501}}); Alphæus, an Israelite

g257.definition: [ἅλων] probably from the base of {{g1507}}; a threshing-floor (as rolled hard), i.e. (figuratively) the grain (and chaff, as just threshed)

g258.definition: [ἀλώπηξ] of uncertain derivation; a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning person

g259.definition: [ἅλωσις] from a collateral form of {{g138}}; capture, be taken.

g260.definition: [ἅμα] a primary particle; properly, at the "same" time, but freely used as a preposition or adverb denoting close association

g261.definition: [ἀμαθής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3129}}; ignorant

g263.definition: [ἀμάραντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3133}}; unfading, i.e. (by implication) perpetual

g264.definition: [ἁμαρτάνω] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g3313}}; properly, to miss the mark (and so not share in the prize), i.e. (figuratively) to err, especially (morally) to sin

g267.definition: [ἀμάρτυρος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a form of {{g3144}}; unattested

g269.definition: [ἄμαχος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3163}}; peaceable

g270.definition: [ἀμάω] from {{g260}}; properly, to collect, i.e. (by implication) reap

g271.definition: [ἀμέθυστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3184}}; the "amethyst" (supposed to prevent intoxication)

g272.definition: [ἀμελέω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3199}}; to be careless of

g273.definition: [ἄμεμπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3201}}; irreproachable

g275.definition: [ἀμέριμνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3308}}; not anxious

g276.definition: [ἀμετάθετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3346}}; unchangeable, or (neuter as abstract) unchangeability

g277.definition: [ἀμετακίνητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3334}}; immovable

g278.definition: [ἀμεταμέλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3338}}; irrevocable

g279.definition: [ἀμετανόητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3340}}; unrepentant

g280.definition: [ἄμετρος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3358}}; immoderate

g281.definition: [ἀμήν] of Hebrew origin ({{h543}}); properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively) trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be it)

g282.definition: [ἀμήτωρ] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3384}}; motherless, i.e. of unknown maternity

g283.definition: [ἀμίαντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3392}}; unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure

g284.definition: [Ἀμιναδάβ] of Hebrew origin ({{h5992}}); Aminadab, an Israelite

g285.definition: [ἄμμος] perhaps from {{g260}}; sand (as heaped on the beach)

g286.definition: [ἀμνός] apparently a primary word; a lamb

g288.definition: [ἄμπελος] probably from the base of {{g297}} and that of {{g257}}; a vine (as coiling about a support)

g289.definition: [ἀμπελουργός] from {{g288}} and {{g2041}}; a vine-worker, i.e. pruner

g291.definition: [Ἀμπλίας] contracted for Latin  (enlarged); Amplias, a Roman Christian

g292.definition: [ἀμύνομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to ward off (for oneself), i.e. protect

g293.definition: [ἀμφίβληστρον] from a compound of the base of {{g297}} and {{g906}}; a (fishing) net (as thrown about the fish)

g294.definition: [ἀμφιέννυμι] from the base of {{g297}} and ἕννυμι (to invest); to enrobe

g295.definition: [Ἀμφίπολις] from the base of {{g297}} and {{g4172}}; a city surrounded by a river; Amphipolis, a place in Macedonia

g296.definition: [ἄμφοδον] from the base of {{g297}} and {{g3598}}; a fork in the road

g298.definition: [ἀμώμητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3469}}; unblamable

g299.definition: [ἄμωμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3470}}; unblemished (literally or figuratively)

g300.definition: [Ἀμών] of Hebrew origin ({{h526}}); Amon, an Israelite
